## Overview

This document defines the escalation policy for the {{team}} team. It outlines how incidents are acknowledged, escalated, and resolved based on severity.

## Severity Levels

| Level | Name | Description | Response SLA | Examples |
|-------|------|-------------|--------------|---------|
| SEV1 | Critical | Complete outage, data loss | 5m ack, 30m resolve | Site down, data breach |
| SEV2 | High | Major feature broken, degraded | 15m ack, 2h resolve | Login broken, payments failing |
| SEV3 | Medium | Minor feature broken | 1h ack, 8h resolve | Search slow, emails delayed |
| SEV4 | Low | Cosmetic, non-urgent | 4h ack, 24h resolve | UI glitch, typo |

