## Escalation Rules

### General Rules

1. **Always acknowledge first** — Even if you can't fix it, acknowledge to show you're aware
2. **Communicate every 15 minutes** during SEV1, every 30 minutes during SEV2
3. **Escalate early** — Don't wait for SLA breach to escalate
4. **Hand off properly** — Document current status before escalating
5. **Keep stakeholders informed** — Use status page and Slack

### Handoff Requirements

Before handing off an incident:
- [ ] Document current status
- [ ] Document what has been tried
- [ ] Document next steps
- [ ] Confirm handoff accepted

### After-Hours Escalation

For after-hours escalations:
1. **SEV1/SEV2**: Immediate phone call to on-call
2. **SEV3/SEV4**: Slack notification, phone if no response within 2x SLA

## Override Rules

In exceptional circumstances, escalation can be skipped:

| Condition | Override |
|-----------|----------|
| All on-call unavailable | Any senior engineer can respond |
| Complete comms outage | Twitter/status page notification |
| Business-critical event | Direct escalation to executive |
| Known issue (already mitigated) | Skip to monitoring |

